pes, and the idiosyncrasies of modern life. Whiny Baby calls on us to simultaneously examine and exult in our brief time on earth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  aCanadian.  aaging.  aangst.  abeauty.  abody.  aenvironment.  afamily.  agrief.  ahonesty.  ajoy.  aliterary.  alove.  alyrical.  amarriage.  anarrative.  apoetry.  apraise.  aquirky.  astruggle.  awhimsical.  awoman.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228020752?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228020752423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228020752/original  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles